		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17094"><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>397 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.69]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree with most of what's been stated previously.&nbsp;&nbsp;It appears you need to upgrade your earrings and your gauntlets first. Gauntlets being the main priority. You need better AC for your hands than the Splitpaw Gloves can provide.  The Darkmail Gaunts are an excellent choice, and shouldn't cost more than 300-350 plat or so. Maybe less. For the money, they are pretty darn hard to beat.<br><br>For Earrings, the Orc Fang or the Cougar Claw are both excellent choices. Orc Fangs now going as low as 100 plat a piece. Either one works great.<br><br>But I would also look at upgrading your bracers.  All that agility is overrated. Pure AC is the way to go.  Each of those Bracers, with it's +9 agility and only +1 AC is "maybe" giving you 4 AC total from each one. You can easily get that AC in just ONE Fine Steel Bracer.  <br><br>In the next 5+ levels, look for a Scavenger Bracer and possibly a Hero Bracer. At level 29 you are getting close to being able to actually do the Hero Bracer quest, with a group, as buying it is quite expensive. The only drawback would be if you are a dwarf. We can't wear the Hero Bracer for some reason.  The Scavenger Bracer though is a nice piece and should run less than 500 plat.  <br><br>But for pure AC, it's hard to beat a fine plate bracer for less than 100 plat.<br><br>Remember, AC is KING!! Forget about all the high stats, agility and Dex. Focus on AC and if you can pick up some stat pluses for Dex, Agility, Wisdom, Strength along the way, then that's even better, but AC FIRST, Stats second.<br><br>JMHO<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>37th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>